President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Inez Moore Tenenbaum as Chair of the Consumer Product Safety Commission (CPSC) and Robert S. Adler as a new Commissioner of the CPSC. The CPSC will receive $107 million in funding, a 71 percent increase since FY 2007. The President plans to expand the Commission to include five Commissioners, with the addition of Robert Adler filling one of the new posts. This expansion is aimed at revitalizing the agency and ensuring a diversity of viewpoints. President Obama emphasized the importance of product safety and expressed confidence in the new leadership to raise the standard of safety. Inez Moore Tenenbaum has experience as South Carolina's State Superintendent of Education and Robert S. Adler is a Professor of Legal Studies with knowledge of CPSC issues.